Day 3 Task: Basic Linux Commands

Task: What is the linux command to

1. To view what's written in a file. - cat
2. To change the access permissions of files. - chmod,chown
3. To check which commands you have run till now. - history
4. To remove a directory/ Folder. - rm -f 
5. To create a fruits.txt file and to view the content. - cat fruits.txt 
6. Add content in devops.txt (One in each line) - Apple, Mango, Banana, Cherry, Kiwi, Orange, Guava. - cat >> devops.txt 
7. To Show only top three fruits from the file. head -3 devops.txt
8. To Show only bottom three fruits from the file. tail -3 devops.txt
9. To create another file Colors.txt and to view the content. cat Colors.txt
10. Add content in Colors.txt (One in each line) - Red, Pink, White, Black, Blue, Orange, Purple, Grey. - cat >> Colors.txt
11. To find the difference between fruits.txt and Colors.txt file. - diff devops.txt Colors.txt
